<p>Thought I&rsquo;d try the <a href="https://atom.io">Atom Editor</a> on my <a href="http://opensuse.org">openSUSE</a> Tumbleweed install.</p>
<p>RPMs and DEB files are available from the Atom site, and the RPM works just fine for me. There&rsquo;s the Markdown for <a href="/post/2015/03/ruby-itunes-ratings-fun/">ruby-itunes-ratings-fun</a>, a live preview, and some sort of Git integration showing up in the sidebar.</p>
<p>Since I&rsquo;m more of a <a href="/card/vim/">card/Vim</a> person, I don&rsquo;t really know what to do with Atom just yet. I may end up not doing much of anything with it. But at least I  now it works. Go ahead and try it out if you&rsquo;re curious.</p>]]></content:encoded>
